But hiatus is practically confined to cases when there is a pause in metre or in sense which at least tones down the harshness. . Thus there may be hiatus at the caesura. Most frequently where hiatus occurs there is a pause in both sense and metre, and,Î‡even where these double pauses coincide, in an overwhelming number of cases there is no hiatus, e.g. when one speaker leaves a line unfinished and another takes it up hiatus is rare.

Hiatus most frequently accompanies breaks in sense when they are considerable, especially if there is a change of speakers.
